criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients:

               -  Diagnosis of bipolar disorder type I or II according to DSM-IV criteria (SCID);

               -  Age between 18-55 years;

               -  Euthymia (YMRS<6 and HMDRS<8) for at least 3 months;

               -  Signed informed consent.

          -  Healthy controls:

               -  No psychiatric diagnosis (SCID);

               -  Age between 18-55 years; euthymia (YMRS<6 and HMDRS<8);

               -  Signed informed consent.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Use of any type of antibiotics, antifungals or pro/prebiotics within at least one
             month prior to recruitment;

          -  IQ<85;

          -  Neurological illness;

          -  Stomach/gut problems;

          -  Current diagnosis of substance abuse or dependence according to DSM-IV criteria
             (SCID);

          -  Electroconvulsive therapy in the last year.
